## 📘 Day 1 - DSA Learning Journey

Welcome to my DSA journey! This is a log of what I learned and practiced on **Day 1**, focusing on building a strong foundation in **Arrays** and **Two Pointer** techniques.
Target: 📌 Crack DSA interviews at top product-based companies.

---

### 📅 Date:

`Day 1`

---

## ✅ Topics Covered

* ✅ Array Basics
* ✅ Finding Maximum Element in Array
* ✅ Second Largest Element
* ✅ Removing Duplicates from Sorted Array
* ✅ Two Pointers (Introduction)
* ✅ Moving Zeros to End
* ✅ Sliding Window (Fixed Size)
* ✅ Time and Space Complexity Analysis
* ✅ Built First LeetCode Medium Solution (Two Sum II)

---

## 🧠 Key Concepts Learned

| Concept                 | Description                                                                                |
| ----------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Time Complexity**     | Learned how to estimate time taken by loops. Eg: `O(n)`, `O(n²)`, dropping constants, etc. |
| **Space Complexity**    | Understood in-place updates vs extra space.                                                |
| **Two Pointer Pattern** | Used to solve problems efficiently when array is sorted or requires pairing logic.         |
| **Sliding Window**      | Learned fixed window technique for subarray/sum problems.                                  |
| **Edge Case Handling**  | Added array size checks, Integer.MIN\_VALUE checks, etc.                                   |
| **Dry Running**         | Practiced stepping through loop iterations manually to debug logic.                        |
| **Confidence Building** | Solved multiple array problems without copying — built logic from scratch.                 |

